arts.ttl: Harrogate Town v Cheltenham Town RECAP: Poor Robins slump to away defeat
arts.sum: Cheltenham Town: Day; Power, Bennett, Stubbs, Adedokun (Miller 63); Kinsella (Backwell 63), Young; Thomas (Taylor 63), Archer, Jude-Boyd; Hay (Williams 63). It was Harrogate's first win over Cheltenham at the fourth attempt and it leaves the Robins 13th, with 31 points from 25 games.

arts.ttl: Harrogate end run of home defeats with victory over Cheltenham
Cheltenham Town 2 Colchester United 1 - reaction from Danny Cowley after defeat
arts.sum: "Unfortunately, if you make two mistakes and you concede two goals away from home, you don't normally win even though we'd done so many good things with the ball against a really aggressive opponent. "We conceded a really bad goal that knocked us and took us a little while to find our rhythm but once we did that, I thought we played some really good football," continued Cowley.

arts.ttl: Bristol City midfielder Tommy Backwell set for Cheltenham Town loan move
arts.sum: Backwell has senior experience in non-league football from youth loans with Hallen and Yate Town, along with a brief spell at National League South club Bath City. Cheltenham Town are set to sign attacking midfielder Tommy Backwell from Bristol City, Gloucestershire Live understands.

Harrogate come into this fixture having won just one of their last nine games, they did win their last league game against Barrow. Cheltenham's 2-1 win over Colchester last time out made it four wins...
